sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT u.user_id) AS total_user_contributors
FROM users u
JOIN contributors c ON u.user_id = c.contributor_id;

SELECT contributor_name
FROM contributors
WHERE contributor_id = 1;

SELECT full_name 
FROM repositories 
WHERE stargazers = (SELECT MAX(stargazers) FROM repositories);

external_knowledge:
- In this context, "gardens" metaphorically represent repositories;
- "Unfinished tasks" refer to open issues in the repositories;
- "Struggling the most" indicates repositories with the highest number of open issues.

sql:
SELECT contributors.contributor_name, repositories.full_name, repositories.stargazers
FROM contributors
INNER JOIN repositories ON contributors.repo_id = repositories.repo_id;

SELECT c.contributor_name, uc.contribution_type, uc.contribution_date 
FROM contributors c 
JOIN user_contributions uc ON c.contributor_id = uc.user_id;

SELECT full_name, stargazers, license
FROM repositories
ORDER BY stargazers DESC;
